 from the Middle English female personal name <i>Rimilde</i>, <i>Rimilda</i>, from Old English or Old Norse <i>Rimhild</i>, perhaps derived from <i><i>hrīm</i></i> ‘frost’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’, or more likely from the corresponding Old Norse words; a <i>(H)rimhild</i> was the wife of Knut Sveinson of Jadar, according to Snorri Sturluson in <i>Heimskringla</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Rimmel","meanings":["English (Middlesex): variant of   Rimel  . This surname is now rare in Britain.","German: variant of <b>Rimmele</b>, from <i>Rümelin</i>, a pet form of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Ruombald</i>, a compound of <i>hruom</i> ‘glory’ + <i>balt</i> ‘bold, brave’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Galfrid de Ridel Count of Blaye was born about 1075, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert Ridel and Agnes heiress of Perigord. He married Geva d'Avranches before 1097. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 25 November 1120, in Barfleur, Manche, Normandy, France, at the age of 46."},"et":{"about 1075–25 November 1120":"umbes 1075–25. november 1120","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1078–1145":"1078–1145","1105–1144":"1105–1144","–1129":"–1129","1062–Female":"1062–Surnud","1129":"1129","1105":"1105","1145":"1145","25 November 1120":"25. november 1120","1144":"1144","1078":"1078","before 1097":"enne 1097","Abt 1105":"umbes 1105","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1062":"1062","about 1075":"umbes 1075","Barfleur, Manche, Normandy, France":"Barfleur, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Stamford, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Drayton Bassett, Staffordshire, England":"Drayton Bassett, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1075–25 November 1120":"noin 1075–25. marraskuuta 1120","1075–1120":"1075–1120","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1078–1145":"1078–1145","1105–1144":"1105–1144","–1129":"–1129","1062–Female":"1